        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 8 at 2:29AM CDT until June 8 at 3:00AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 229 AM CDT, automated weather equipment reported a severe
thunderstorm was located over Canyon, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Tennis ball size hail and 70 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Automated weather equipment in Umbarger recorded 72 mph
wind gust.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings. People and animals outdoors will
be injured. Expect hail damage to roofs, siding, windows,
and vehicles.

Locations impacted include...
Umbarger, Mescalero Park, Buffalo Lake, Palo Duro Canyon, and Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
